# WHAT IT IS
#   remindee-bot is "a reminder bot for Telegram without bullshit"
#   — a self-hostable Telegram bot that lets a user type
#   reminders in natural-language English/Russian/etc. (parsed
#   via the workspace-bundled `remindee-parser` crate) and
#   schedules them through cron and one-shot timers backed by a
#   SQLite database persisted via sea-orm.  The bot reads its
#   `BOT_TOKEN` from CLI or env, opens a teloxide
#   `sqlite-storage-rustls` session against the configured
#   `REMINDEE_DB`, and runs a polling-based update loop with the
#   `tokio` runtime.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli.rs `Cli` struct —
#                       clap 4 with derive feature)
#   remindee-bot [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -d, --database <FILE>          Path to the SQLite database
#                                    file (created if missing)
#                                    [env: REMINDEE_DB; default:
#                                    $XDG_DATA_HOME/remindee_db.
#                                    sqlite]
#     -t, --token <BOT_TOKEN>        Telegram bot token
#                                    [env: BOT_TOKEN]
#     -s, --sqlite-max-connections <N>
#                                    Maximum SQLite connection
#                                    pool size
#                                    [env: SQLITE_MAX_CONNECTIONS
#                                    — default: 1]
#
#   Standard clap auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `teloxide = { version = "0.17", features
#   = ["macros", "sqlite-storage-rustls"] }` declared in
#   Cargo.toml — `teloxide` is THE canonical Rust Telegram Bot
#   framework maintained by the teloxide org (teloxide/teloxide,
#   4.1K stars, the Rust counterpart of python-telegram-bot /
#   node-telegram-bot-api).  teloxide exposes the
#   `teloxide::Bot` HTTP transport, the
#   `teloxide::dispatching::Dispatcher` typed-handler builder,
#   filter combinators (`Update::filter_message`,
#   `Update::filter_callback_query`,
#   `Update::filter_inline_query`,
#   `Update::filter_my_chat_member`,
#   `Update::filter_chat_member`,
#   `Update::filter_chosen_inline_result`), pluggable storage
#   backends (`InMemStorage`, `SqliteStorage`, `RedisStorage`,
#   `ErasedStorage`), the `teloxide_macros` proc-macro suite
#   for `BotCommand` enum derivation, FSM dialogue support
#   (`Dialogue<S, T>`), MarkdownV2 / HTML / MessageBuilder
#   helpers, file-upload helpers, custom keyboard / inline
#   keyboard / login URL button construction, and the
#   `tokio`-native async runtime.  remindee-bot's `bot::run()`
#   constructs a typed `Bot` from the configured token, opens
#   a `SqliteStorage` against the configured database, and
#   wires the natural-language reminder parser into a
#   `Dispatcher`.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/magnickolas/remindee-bot/contents/
#         Cargo.toml
#       → [dependencies.teloxide] version = "0.17"
#         features = ["macros", "sqlite-storage-rustls"]
#       → [package] name = "remindee-bot"
#         license = "GPL-3.0-only"
#     gh api repos/magnickolas/remindee-bot/contents/src/cli.rs
#       → struct Cli { database: PathBuf, token: String,
#                       sqlite_max_connections: u32 }
#       → #[arg(short, long, env = "REMINDEE_DB", ...)]
#       → #[arg(short, long, env = "BOT_TOKEN")]
#       → #[arg(short, long, env = "SQLITE_MAX_CONNECTIONS",
#                default_value = "1")]
#   This entry is the Rust=145 leader bump that OPENS Axis 90
#   (Telegram Bot API / teloxide) at 1/0/0.  Pairing Go and
#   TS-Node bumps will follow at R950 and R951 (Go=145
#   candidates go-telegram-bot-api/telegram-bot-api-based
#   CLIs; TS-Node=145 candidates grammyjs/grammy or telegraf
#   users).
#
#   No completion for `remindee-bot` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_remindee-bot() {
    _arguments -s \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
        '(-d --database)'{-d,--database}'=[SQLite database file path]:file:_files -g "*.sqlite"' \
        '(-t --token)'{-t,--token}'=[Telegram bot token]:token:' \
        '(-s --sqlite-max-connections)'{-s,--sqlite-max-connections}'=[max SQLite connections]:n:'
}

_remindee-bot "$@"
